20/11/2005
TETOVO, Macedonia -- Ali Ahmeti was re-elected as the leader of the main ethnic Albanian political formation in Macedonia, the Democratic Union for Integration, during a party congress in Tetovo Saturday (19 November).
Speaking after his re-election, Ahmeti said the country's political stability remains his top priority.
In other news, five individuals -- three Macedonian and two Greek citizens -- have been detained for drug trafficking in a joint operation by the Macedonian and Greek police, the Macedonian Interior Ministry announced Saturday.
The five were arrested after trying to smuggle 10.5 kg of cocaine via the border crossing at Novo Selo.
(A1 TV, Telma TV, Makfax - 19/11/05)
